<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://gohugo.io/" version="0.85.0">Hugo</generator><title type="html">docker hub on ilo</title><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/docker-hub/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="HTML"/><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/docker-hub/index.xml" rel="alternate" type="application/rss+xml" title="RSS"/><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/docker-hub/atom.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml" title="Atom"/><updated>2021-07-12T04:56:11+00:00</updated><id>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/tags/docker-hub/</id><entry><title type="html">Container Registries</title><link href="https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/integration/container-registries/?utm_source=atom_feed" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><id>https://ilo.projects.metio.wtf/integration/container-registries/</id><published>2020-04-13T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2020-04-13T00:00:00+00:00</updated><content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>In order to share build environments within a team, using a <a href="https://github.com/opencontainers/distribution-spec">container registry</a> is highly recommended.</p>
<h2 id="docker-hub">Docker Hub</h2>
<p><a href="https://hub.docker.com/">Docker Hub</a> has an <a href="https://docs.docker.com/docker-hub/builds/">automated build system</a> that can be used to automatically create a build environment which in turn can be used by team members of your project.</p>
<p>Make sure Docker Hub rebuilds your build environment on every change to main (or any other branch) and have your contributors pull the resulting images to their machines.</p>
<h2 id="github-container-registry">GitHub Container Registry</h2>
<p>The <a href="https://github.blog/2020-09-01-introducing-github-container-registry/">GitHub container registry</a> can be used together with <a href="https://github.com/features/actions">GitHub actions</a> to publish OCI images for your team. Simply follow their getting started <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/packages/getting-started-with-github-container-registry/migrating-to-github-container-registry-for-docker-images">guide</a> to publish your image(s).</p>
